                  <span class="tag-dot"></span>
                  <span>Disabled</span>
                  <span class="tag-close"><svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg></span>
                </span>
              </div>

              <!-- With Close vs Without Close -->
              <div class="demo-group-label" style="margin-top: 16px;">With Close vs Without Close</div>
              <div class="demo-tag-row">
                <span class="tag-demo tag-md tag-primary">
                  <span class="tag-dot"></span>
                  <span>With Close</span>
                  <span class="tag-close"><svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg></span>
                </span>
                <span class="tag-demo tag-md tag-primary">
                  <span class="tag-dot"></span>
                  <span>Without Close</span>
                </span>
              </div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Do & Don't -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="do-dont" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
          <div class="do-dont-grid">
            <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use tags for user-generated or user-selectable labels (filters, categories, selections).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Keep label text short (1-3 words).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Show Close for dismissible tags in multi-select fields or filter bars.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use consistent semantic variants across the application for the same meaning.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use the Outline variant when tags appear over colored or patterned backgrounds.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Status Indicator as the leading element to combine status communication with labeling.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use tags for non-interactive status display (use Badge instead).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use more than 2-3 words in a tag label.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't mix semantic variant colors arbitrarily within the same context.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't disable the close button while keeping the tag interactive; disable the entire tag instead.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use tags as primary navigation elements.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div> <!-- End tab-overview -->

      <!-- ═══ STYLE TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-style" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">
        <h2 id="style-overview" class="doc-section-title">Style</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Design tokens, color mappings, and sizing specifications that define the Tag's visual language.</p>

        <!-- Variant Axes -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="variant-axes" class="doc-section-title">Variant Axes</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Tag component is built from five independent variant axes, producing a comprehensive matrix of 432 unique combinations.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Variant:</strong> 6 options &mdash; Neutral, Primary, Success, Warning, Error, Outline</li>
            <li><strong>Size:</strong> 3 options &mdash; Small, Medium, Large</li>
            <li><strong>State:</strong> 4 options &mdash; Default, Hover, Focus, Disabled</li>
            <li><strong>RTL:</strong> 2 options &mdash; False, True</li>
            <li><strong>Leading Element:</strong> 3 options &mdash; None, Status Indicator, Icon</li>
            <li><strong>Total:</strong> 6 &times; 3 &times; 4 &times; 2 &times; 3 = <strong>432 variants</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Semantic Variants -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="semantic-variants" class="doc-section-title">Semantic Variants</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Each variant communicates a distinct semantic meaning through its color palette. Filled variants use a tinted background with darker text; the Outline variant uses a transparent background with a visible border.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Variant</th><th>Hue</th><th>Usage</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Neutral</strong></td><td>Grey</td><td>General-purpose, no specific semantic meaning.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Primary</strong></td><td>Blue</td><td>Active selections, primary categorization.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Success</strong></td><td>Green</td><td>Positive or confirmed status tags.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Warning</strong></td><td>Amber/Orange</td><td>Tags requiring attention or caution.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Error</strong></td><td>Red</td><td>Error, critical, or rejected state.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Outline</strong></td><td>Grey (border)</td><td>Low-emphasis tags on colored or busy backgrounds.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Sizes -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="sizes" class="doc-section-title">Sizes</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Three sizes to fit different layout contexts.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Size</th><th>Usage</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Small</strong></td><td>Compact layouts, table cells, inline metadata, filter chips.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Medium</strong></td><td>Default size for most contexts, form fields, toolbars.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Large</strong></td><td>Standalone tags, page headers, prominent filter selections.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- States -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="states" class="doc-section-title">States</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Tags cycle through four states, each with distinct visual treatments to communicate interactivity.</p>
          <div class="state-grid">
            <div class="state-card">
              <span class="tag-demo tag-md tag-primary"><span class="tag-dot"></span><span>Tag</span><span class="tag-close"><svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg></span></span>
              <div class="state-card-title">Default</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Standard resting state</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <span class="tag-demo tag-md tag-primary tag-hover"><span class="tag-dot"></span><span>Tag</span><span class="tag-close"><svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg></span></span>
              <div class="state-card-title">Hover</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Background darkens slightly</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <span class="tag-demo tag-md tag-primary" style="outline: 2px solid #2C66DD; outline-offset: 2px;"><span class="tag-dot"></span><span>Tag</span><span class="tag-close"><svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg></span></span>
              <div class="state-card-title">Focus</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Visible focus ring indicator</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <span class="tag-demo tag-md tag-primary tag-disabled"><span class="tag-dot"></span><span>Tag</span><span class="tag-close"><svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg></span></span>
              <div class="state-card-title">Disabled</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">45% opacity, no interaction</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Design Tokens -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="design-tokens" class="doc-h3">Design Tokens<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">Tokens</span></h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Value</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>tag-border-radius</code></td><td>6px</td><td>Corner radius for all tag sizes</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-font-family</code></td><td>Zoho Puvi</td><td>Primary font family</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-font-weight</code></td><td>500 (Medium)</td><td>Font weight for label text</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-sm-padding</code></td><td>2px 8px</td><td>Padding for small size</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-md-padding</code></td><td>4px 10px</td><td>Padding for medium size</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-lg-padding</code></td><td>6px 14px</td><td>Padding for large size</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-sm-font-size</code></td><td>11px / 16px</td><td>Font size / line height for small</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-md-font-size</code></td><td>12px / 18px</td><td>Font size / line height for medium</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-lg-font-size</code></td><td>14px / 20px</td><td>Font size / line height for large</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-gap</code></td><td>6px</td><td>Gap between internal elements</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-dot-size</code></td><td>6px (8px lg)</td><td>Status indicator dot diameter</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-close-size</code></td><td>12px (14px lg)</td><td>Close icon size</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>tag-disabled-opacity</code></td><td>0.45</td><td>Opacity when disabled</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ USAGE TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

        <!-- When to Use -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When to Use</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Tags are best suited for compact, interactive labels that users can add, remove, or filter by.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Categorization:</strong> Label items with categories such as department, type, or priority.</li>
            <li><strong>Filtering:</strong> Represent active filter selections in search bars or filter panels.</li>
            <li><strong>Metadata:</strong> Display metadata values like status, owner, or version inline with content.</li>
            <li><strong>Multi-select inputs:</strong> Show selected values as dismissible tags inside combo boxes or multi-select fields.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Leading Element -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="leading-element" class="doc-section-title">Leading Element</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Tags support an optional leading element to add visual context before the label text.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>None</strong></td><td>No leading element. Only label and optional close button.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Status Indicator</strong></td><td>A small colored dot before the label. Useful for showing inline status.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Icon</strong></td><td>A swappable icon before the label. Useful for adding visual context.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- RTL Support -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="rtl-support" class="doc-section-title">RTL Support</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Tag component fully supports right-to-left languages with automatic layout mirroring.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Layout direction:</strong> Mirrored &mdash; leading element moves to trailing, close button to leading.</li>
            <li><strong>Text alignment:</strong> Adjusted to follow natural RTL reading order.</li>
            <li><strong>Spacing and padding:</strong> Mirrored to maintain consistent visual balance.</li>
            <li><strong>RTL Label property:</strong> Uses the dedicated RTL Label text property for localized content.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Tag vs Related Components -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="comparison" class="doc-section-title">Tag vs Related Components</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Understanding when to use a Tag versus similar components.</p>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Usage</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Badge</strong></td><td>Non-interactive label for status display.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Counter</strong></td><td>Numeric count indicator.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Status Indicator</strong></td><td>Dot + label for minimal status.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Button</strong></td><td>Use for actions; tags represent objects/values.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Related Components -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="related-components" class="doc-section-title">Related Components</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or can be used alongside the Tag.</p>
          <div class="related-grid">
            <a href="Badges.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="4"/></svg> Badge</a>
            <a href="Counter.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="8" width="18" height="8" rx="4"/></svg> Counter</a>
            <a href="Status-indicator.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="5"/></svg> Status Indicator</a>
            <a href="Button.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="3"/></svg> Button</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Figma Reference -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="figma-reference" class="doc-section-title">Figma Reference</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Design specifications and Figma component details for developer handoff.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Figma Node:</strong> <code style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet);">16462:101691</code> &mdash; File: UEMS - Design System 3.0</li>
            <li><strong>Example variant string:</strong> <code style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet);">Variant=Primary, Size=Medium, State=Default, RTL=False, Leading Element=Icon</code></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- ═══ CODE TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-code" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">
        <h2 id="live-demo-code" class="doc-section-title">Live demo (Code)</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Configure the Tag and view the generated HTML.</p>

        <style>
          .tag-playground { border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; background: var(--prism-surface); margin-bottom: 48px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); }
          [data-theme="light"] .tag-playground { background: #fff; border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.1); box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(37,99,235,0.08); }
          .tag-pg-toolbar { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; padding: 16px 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border); background: var(--prism-surface-hover); }
          [data-theme="light"] .tag-pg-toolbar { background: rgba(248, 250, 255, 0.6); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.1); }
          .tag-pg-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; flex: 1; min-width: 140px; }
          .tag-pg-label { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text-muted); }
          .tag-pg-select, .tag-pg-input { background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); color: var(--prism-text); padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 8px; outline: none; font-family: inherit; font-size: 14px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; }
          [data-theme="light"] .tag-pg-select, [data-theme="light"] .tag-pg-input { background: #fff; border-color: rgba(37,99,235,0.15); color: #1e293b; }
          .tag-pg-select:focus, .tag-pg-input:focus { border-color: var(--prism-violet); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(37,99,235,0.15); }
          .tag-pg-preview { padding: 60px; min-height: 180px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: #0a0a0c; background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255,255,255,0.1) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 20px 20px; }
          [data-theme="light"] .tag-pg-preview { background: #ffffff; background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(37,99,235,0.08) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 20px 20px; }
          .tag-pg-code-header { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 12px 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border-top: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border); }
          [data-theme="light"] .tag-pg-code-header { background: rgba(248, 250, 255, 0.8); border-color: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); }
          .tag-pg-copy { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; background: transparent; border: none; font-family: inherit; font-size: 13.5px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--prism-text-muted); cursor: pointer; padding: 6px 12px; border-radius: 6px; transition: all 0.2s; }
          .tag-pg-copy:hover { background: var(--prism-surface-hover); color: var(--prism-text); }
          [data-theme="light"] .tag-pg-copy:hover { background: rgba(37,99,235,0.08); color: var(--prism-violet); }
          .tag-pg-code { background: #0a0a0c; padding: 24px; overflow-x: auto; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0; white-space: pre; }
          .tag-pg-code .tk-tag { color: #a78bfa; }
          .tag-pg-code .tk-attr { color: #38bdf8; }
          .tag-pg-code .tk-str { color: #34d399; }
          .tag-pg-code .tk-punct { color: #94a3b8; }
        </style>

        <div class="tag-playground">
          <div class="tag-pg-toolbar">
            <div class="tag-pg-group">
              <label class="tag-pg-label">Variant</label>
              <select class="tag-pg-select" id="tag-pg-variant">
                <option value="neutral">Neutral</option>
                <option value="primary" selected>Primary</option>
                <option value="success">Success</option>
                <option value="warning">Warning</option>
                <option value="error">Error</option>
                <option value="outline">Outline</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="tag-pg-group">
              <label class="tag-pg-label">Size</label>
              <select class="tag-pg-select" id="tag-pg-size">
                <option value="sm">Small</option>
                <option value="md" selected>Medium</option>
                <option value="lg">Large</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="tag-pg-group">
              <label class="tag-pg-label">Leading</label>
              <select class="tag-pg-select" id="tag-pg-leading">
                <option value="none">None</option>
                <option value="dot" selected>Status dot</option>
                <option value="icon">Icon</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="tag-pg-group">
              <label class="tag-pg-label">Close button</label>
              <select class="tag-pg-select" id="tag-pg-close">
                <option value="on" selected>Show</option>
                <option value="off">Hide</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="tag-pg-group">
              <label class="tag-pg-label">Label</label>
              <input class="tag-pg-input" id="tag-pg-text" type="text" value="Design">
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tag-pg-preview">
            <span class="tag-demo tag-md tag-primary" id="tag-pg-preview"></span>
          </div>

          <div class="tag-pg-code-header">
            <div style="font-size: 13.5px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text);">HTML</div>
            <button class="tag-pg-copy" id="tag-pg-copy-btn">
              <svg width="15" height="15" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8 7v8a2 2 0 002 2h6M8 7V5a2 2 0 012-2h4.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l4.414 4.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V15a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2M8 7H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h8a2 2 0 002-2v-2"/></svg>
              Copy code
            </button>
          </div>
          <pre class="tag-pg-code" id="tag-pg-code"></pre>
        </div>

        <script>
          (function(){
            const el = {
              variant: document.getElementById('tag-pg-variant'),
              size: document.getElementById('tag-pg-size'),
              leading: document.getElementById('tag-pg-leading'),
              close: document.getElementById('tag-pg-close'),
              text: document.getElementById('tag-pg-text'),
              preview: document.getElementById('tag-pg-preview'),
              code: document.getElementById('tag-pg-code'),
              copy: document.getElementById('tag-pg-copy-btn')
            };
            if (!el.preview) return;

            const ICON_SVG = '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M8 12h8M12 8v8"/></svg>';
            const CLOSE_SVG = '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M18 6L6 18M6 6l12 12"/></svg>';

            function escape(s){ return s.replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;'); }

            function render(){
              const variant = el.variant.value;
              const size = el.size.value;
              const leading = el.leading.value;
              const showClose = el.close.value === 'on';
              const label = el.text.value || 'Tag';
              const classes = ['tag-demo', 'tag-' + size, 'tag-' + variant];

              let inner = '';
              if (leading === 'dot') inner += '<span class="tag-dot"></span>';
              else if (leading === 'icon') inner += '<span class="tag-icon">' + ICON_SVG + '</span>';
              inner += '<span>' + escape(label) + '</span>';
              if (showClose) inner += '<span class="tag-close">' + CLOSE_SVG + '</span>';

              el.preview.className = classes.join(' ');
              el.preview.innerHTML = inner;

              const classAttr = classes.join(' ');
              let parts = [];
              parts.push('<span class="tk-punct">&lt;</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span> <span class="tk-attr">class</span><span class="tk-punct">=</span><span class="tk-str">"' + classAttr + '"</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>');
              if (leading === 'dot') parts.push('  <span class="tk-punct">&lt;</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span> <span class="tk-attr">class</span><span class="tk-punct">=</span><span class="tk-str">"tag-dot"</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>');
              else if (leading === 'icon') parts.push('  <span class="tk-punct">&lt;</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span> <span class="tk-attr">class</span><span class="tk-punct">=</span><span class="tk-str">"tag-icon"</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>...<span class="tk-punct">&lt;/</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>');
              parts.push('  <span class="tk-punct">&lt;</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>' + escape(label) + '<span class="tk-punct">&lt;/</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>');
              if (showClose) parts.push('  <span class="tk-punct">&lt;</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span> <span class="tk-attr">class</span><span class="tk-punct">=</span><span class="tk-str">"tag-close"</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>...<span class="tk-punct">&lt;/</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>');
              parts.push('<span class="tk-punct">&lt;/</span><span class="tk-tag">span</span><span class="tk-punct">&gt;</span>');
              el.code.innerHTML = parts.join('\n');
            }
            ['variant','size','leading','close'].forEach(k => el[k].addEventListener('change', render));
            el.text.addEventListener('input', render);
            el.copy.addEventListener('click', () => {
              navigator.clipboard.writeText(el.code.innerText).then(() => {
                const orig = el.copy.innerHTML;
                el.copy.innerHTML = '<svg width="15" height="15" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Copied';
                setTimeout(() => { el.copy.innerHTML = orig; }, 1800);
              });
            });
            render();
          })();
        </script>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <h2 id="code-overview" class="doc-section-title">Code</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Component properties, variant axes, and instance override instructions for the Tag component.</p>

        <!-- Component Properties -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="component-properties" class="doc-h3">Component Properties</h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><code>Show Close</code></td><td>Boolean</td><td>true</td><td>Toggles the close/dismiss button visibility.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Label</code></td><td>Text</td><td>"Tag"</td><td>The display text (LTR).</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>RTL Label</code></td><td>Text</td><td>"\u0648\u0633\u0645"</td><td>The display text (RTL).</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Status Indicator</code></td><td>Instance Swap</td><td>Default indicator</td><td>Swappable status indicator instance.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><code>Leading Icon</code></td><td>Instance Swap</td><td>Default icon</td><td>Swappable icon instance.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Variant Axis Reference -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="variant-axis-reference" class="doc-h3">Variant Axis Reference</h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Axis</th><th>Values</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Variant</strong></td><td>Neutral, Primary, Success, Warning, Error, Outline</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Size</strong></td><td>Small, Medium, Large</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>State</strong></td><td>Default, Hover, Focus, Disabled</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>RTL</strong></td><td>False, True</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Leading Element</strong></td><td>None, Status Indicator, Icon</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Instance Overrides -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="instance-overrides" class="doc-h3">Instance Overrides</h3>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Steps to customize a Tag instance in your design tool or codebase.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>1.</strong> Select the Tag instance.</li>
            <li><strong>2.</strong> Toggle Show Close on/off.</li>
            <li><strong>3.</strong> Edit the Label text directly.</li>
            <li><strong>4.</strong> Change Leading Element variant to add icon or status indicator.</li>
            <li><strong>5.</strong> Swap the Leading Icon or Status Indicator.</li>
            <li><strong>6.</strong> Toggle RTL for right-to-left language support.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
